def MAPE(y_true, y_pred): 
    y_true, y_pred = np.array(y_true), np.array(y_pred)
    return np.around((np.mean(np.abs((y_true - y_pred) / y_true))*100), decimals=2)

part e of the question¶

In [ ]:
import cvxpy as cp
In [ ]:
def loss_fn(X, Y, beta):
    return cp.norm2(cp.matmul(X, beta) - Y)**2

def ridge_penalty(beta):
    return cp.norm1(beta)**2

def fused_lasso(beta):
    return sum(cp.norm1(beta[i+1] - beta[i]) for i in range(len(beta)-1))

def objective_fn(X, Y, beta, lambda1, lambda2):
    return loss_fn(X, Y, beta) + lambda1 * ridge_penalty(beta) + lambda2 * fused_lasso(beta)

def mse(X, Y, beta):
    return (1.0 / X.shape[0]) * loss_fn(X, Y, beta).value
In [ ]:
